news.title: Kolkata: Construction materials eat into New Town road space
news.para: “We will send notices to the contractors, asking them to remove the debris or we will impose fine on the offenders,” said a NKDA official.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment's GIS mapping of properties stuck in limbo
news.para: When GHMC initiated GIS mapping of properties and synced it with the digital house numbering project, SCB officials, who were impressed with the neighbouring civic body’s idea, also decided to take up a similar exercise and proposed it five years ago.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh mining department violated norms in sand mining: NGT panel
news.para: The APMDC levied a fine of Rs 1 lakh on contractor PMR Infra India Private Ltd for violating the terms of the contract. The joint committee said the APMDC carried out sand excavation in river Araniar at Sururupalli in Chittoor district to extract sand for local needs.

news.title: No house sites on hillocks, says Andhra Pradesh HC
news.para: Social activists S Maheswari and Y Vijayalakshmi filed separate petitions challenging the action of the tahsildar allotting 10 acres of hillock land for the purpose of giving house sites under Navaratnalu - Pedalandariki Illu scheme.

news.title: Over 90 construction & demolition sites shut down for violating dust norms in Delhi
news.para: A senior DPCC official said, “All the C&D sites, which have been closed down on Friday, are over 500 square metre. They include sites of both government and private agencies.”

news.title: Need-based changes relief in CHB flats unlikely before Chandigarh civic body polls
news.para: The board had formed a committee to regularise building violations in CHB dwelling units on the Delhi pattern of one-time settlement on September 8.

news.title: Hyderabad: HMDA to conduct e-auctions for 44 open plots near Nagole
news.para: Authorities chose Uppal Bhagat layout as it is a safe bet for the government on various counts. There are also no legal hitches on the land and it received good response from the bidders in the two phases of land auctions that were held in 2019.

news.title: Builder can't force buyer to take possession of incomplete flat: NCDRC
news.para: In this case, the buyer— Suman Kumar Jha and Pratibha Jha— had booked in 2013 a 3,900 sqft luxurious villa in the project launched by Mantri Technology Constellation Private Limited in Chennai.

news.title: Guangzhou, Shenzhen told to allocate 10% of land for affordable rental homes
news.para: Under proposed new rules, rental housing will focus on the development of homes no larger than 70 square metres in area for new residents and young people.

news.title: House prices in UK jump 0.9% in October: Halifax
news.para: It brought the average house price to 270,027 pounds ($364,374)- up 8.1% on October 2020 and marking the strongest annual growth rate for four months.

news.title: Chinese banks quicken home loan disbursement but caution prevails
news.para: Authorities do not want genuine buyers to be shut out of the market or developers to face delays in receiving payments due to slow loan disbursements in a market whose health is key to the economy.

news.title: Residential buildings with EV charging stations may see price rise of 2-5%: JLL
news.para: Depending on type of buildings, these retrofit projects will have a major impact on pricing of residential asset class and will also help in efficient utilisation of real estate.

news.title: Demand for houses in Mysuru spikes as on-campus classes resume
news.para: For instance, in Bogadi, RR Nagar, Dattagalli and Vijayanagar areas in Mysuru city, rent for a two-bedroom house, which was between Rs 8,000 to Rs 10,000, has now increased to anywhere between Rs 11,000 and Rs 12,000.

news.title: Rising rents taking up growing share of Americans' income
news.para: Households with a median U.S. rent of $1,179 in August tapped 30.3% of their monthly income to pay their rent, up from 29.4% a year earlier, according to an analysis by Zillow.

news.title: Tiny house in wealthy Boston suburb sells for $315,000
news.para: The roughly 250-square-foot (23-square-meter) home in Newton sold on Monday for $315,000, according to Coldwell Banker Realty's Hans Brings Results agency.
